0how%20a%20culinary%20aficionado%20would%20describe%20the%20vermicelli.%20In%20Italy%2C%20the%20vermicelli%20features%20in%20both%20sweet%20and%20savoury%20dishes.%20When%20mixed%20with%20tomatoes%2C%20garlic%20and%20anchovies%2C%20it%20makes%20for%20great%20spaghetti%2C%20while%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F308752%2Fdodha-barfi-history-story-of-wrestler-harbans-vig-tales-of-taste-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E14th-century%20recipe%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlighted%20how%20it%20blended%20well%20with%20wheat%20flour%2C%20almonds%2C%20eggs%20and%20sugar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201770%20American%20cookbook%20%E2%80%98The%20Art%20of%20Cookery%E2%80%99%20spoke%20of%20how%20the%20vermicelli%20made%20an%20excellent%20meal%20when%20blended%20well%20with%20egg%20yolks%20and%20flour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsian%20cuisine%20embraced%20vermicelli%20and%20its%20many%20forms%20right%20since%20the%20Qin%20dynasty%20dating%20back%20to%20221%20BCE%3B%20whether%20as%20%3Cem%3Emi%20fen%3C%2Fem%3E%20(rice%20noodles)%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emung%20bean%20vermicelli%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cellophane%20or%20glass%20noodles)%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emisua%3C%2Fem%3E%20(wheat-based%20vermicelli).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20the%20Indian%20variations%20of%20vermicelli%2C%20local%20lore%20tells%20us%20that%20the%20only%20way%20perhaps%20that%20vermicelli%20made%20its%20way%20into%20the%20subcontinent%20is%20through%20trade%20networks%20extending%20between%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20Egypt%2C%20the%20technique%20of%20frying%20vermicelli%20(%3Cem%3Eshe%E2%80%99reya%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20butter%20or%20oil%20was%20prevalent.%20Once%20fried%2C%20water%20would%20be%20added%20to%20the%20fried%20noodles%20and%20it%20would%20be%20cooked%20with%20rice.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261268%2Fbiryani-map-of-india-taste-the-history-find-your-favourite-among-28-versions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20hearty%20meal%3C%2Fa%3E!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20article%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0explores%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20sweet%20dish.%20Hand%20rolling%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20was%20once%20a%20traditional%20occupation%2C%20gained%20popularity%20during%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Mughal%20rule.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20said%20that%20Emperor%20Humayun%20ignited%20the%20love%20for%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20court%20by%20reintroducing%20the%20Persian%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekurma%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edum%20ki%20seviyan.%20%3C%2Fem%3EBut%2C%20it%20was%C2%A0Emperor%20Shah%20Jahan%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20the%20dish%20becoming%20its%20current%20version%20with%20spices%2C%20ghee%20and%20dry%20fruits.%20An%20anecdote%20often%20told%20is%20how%20the%20Emperor%20requested%20a%20special%20sunset-coloured%C2%A0%3Cem%3Evarq%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(an%20edible%20foil%20garnishing)%20to%20accompany%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20tradition%20lasted%20until%20the%20time%20of%20Bahadur%20Shah%20Zafar%20who%20would%20prepare%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20ingredient%20entered%20India%2C%20it%20was%20local%20palate%20preferences%20that%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20many%20vermicelli-based%20dishes%20that%20now%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Oxford%20Companion%20to%20Food%E2%80%99%20by%20Alan%20Davidson%20and%20Tom%20Jaine%2C%20says%20the%20following%20about%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20The%20Sanskrit%20name%20for%20noodles%20is%20%3Cem%3Esevika%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20may%20derive%20from%20an%20unrecorded%20word%20meaning%20thread%20connected%20with%20the%20root%20%3Cem%3Esiv%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20sewing.%20%3Cem%3ESev%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20crisp%20fried%20noodles%20prepared%20from%20%3Cem%3Ebesan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea)%20flour.%20%3Cem%3ESeviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(also%20%3Cem%3Eseviya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Esivayya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eshavayi%3C%2Fem%3E)%20usually%20refers%20to%20a%20sweet%20dish%20of%20vermicelli%20noodles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20637px)%20100vw%2C%20637px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22637%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20sheer%20khurma%20is%20a%20premium%20variety%20of%20seviyan%20prepared%20with%20khoya%20and%20dry%20fruits%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593.jpg%20637w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593-270x300.jpg%20270w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593-500x557.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-1712583593-150x167.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346837%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22709%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20sheer%20khurma%20is%20a%20premium%20variety%20of%20seviyan%20prepared%20with%20khoya%20and%20dry%20fruits%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Ftashasartisanfoods%2Fp%2FCrVj0KFSPP4%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETashas%20Artisan%20Foods%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20enter%20India%2C%20you%20are%20certain%20to%20get%20a%20whiff%20of%20the%20aromas%20of%20multiple%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345374%2Ftraditional-karnataka-food-recipes-adukale-sankethi-cuisine-read-to-eat-poha-upma-bisi-bele-bath-sambar-powder%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelicious%20preparations%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20feature%20vermicelli%20as%20the%20hero%20ingredient.%20Known%20as%20%3Cem%3Eshavige%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Esemiya%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Esevalu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20vermicelli%20in%20India%20takes%20on%20new%20avatars%20as%20we%20go%20from%20South%20to%20North%20and%20East%20to%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20breakfast%20in%20South%20India%20is%20complete%20without%20an%20order%20for%20%3Cem%3Esemiya%20upma%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20dish%20made%20with%20a%20mixture%20of%20vermicelli%20and%20vegetables)%2C%20while%20in%20the%20North%20the%20fuss-free%20%3Cem%3Enamkeen%20seviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(savoury%20vermicelli)%20has%20many%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20South%20or%20North%2C%20everyone%20concedes%20that%20there%20is%20no%20rival%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%20kheer%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20vermicelli%20pudding%20made%20with%20%3Cem%3Eghee%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20rice%20vermicelli%20noodles%2C%20milk%2C%20spices%2C%20and%20a%20sweetener).%20And%20that%20brings%20us%20back%20to%20our%20Eid%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHistory%20sprinkled%20with%20a%20dash%20of%20sweetness%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVermicelli%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20India%20was%20marked%20by%20every%20region%20putting%20its%20own%20spin%20on%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F281110%2Fmithai-map-of-india-10-lesser-known-indian-sweets-you-must-try-at-least-once%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20West%2C%20adding%20saffron%20and%20chopped%20nuts%20to%20the%20vermicelli%20is%20a%20common%20practice%20while%20in%20the%20North%2C%20this%20is%20substituted%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekhoya%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20the%20South%2C%20coconut%20milk%20is%20added%20to%20get%20a%20thick%20consistency%20while%20those%20in%20Odisha%20and%20West%20Bengal%20prefer%20adding%20rosewater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20vermicelli%20is%20cooked%20depends%20upon%20the%20festive%20occasion%20too.%20For%20instance%2C%20during%20Raksha%20Bandhan%2C%20some%20people%20prepare%20%3Cem%3Emeethe%20java%3C%2Fem%3E%20(vermicelli%20pudding).%20The%20%E2%80%9Causpicious%E2%80%9D%20short%20noodles%20used%20in%20the%20dish%20are%20a%20version%20of%20the%20thinner%2C%20longer%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F285541%2Fsabja-seed-health-benefits-weight-loss-recipe-indian-food%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeloved%20summer%20drink%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Efalooda%3C%2Fem%3E%20features%20thicker%20glutinous%20strands%20of%20vermicelli%20dunked%20into%20a%20syrup%20and%20served%20with%20ice%20cream.%20The%20dessert%20traces%20back%20to%20%3Cem%3Efaloodeh%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20Persian%20cuisine%20where%20the%20vermicelli%20would%20be%20made%20from%20frozen%20cornstarch%2C%20mixed%20with%20rose%20water%2C%20lime%20juice%20and%20pistachios.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20too%2C%20there%20are%20different%20varieties.%20I%20recall%20Eid%20feasts%20with%20friends%2C%20where%20half%20of%20the%20group%20preferred%20the%20flowy%20version%20of%20the%20dessert%20(which%20resembled%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekheer%3C%2Fem%3E%20cooked%20with%20milk)%2C%20and%20the%20other%20half%20would%20argue%20that%20the%20dry%20version%20(vermicelli%20sweet%20made%20by%20frying%20the%20noodles%20in%20ghee%2C%20adding%20syrup%20and%20nuts)%20was%20more%20delicious.%20I%20belonged%20to%20the%20former!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhatever%20your%20preference%20for%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20suffices%20to%20say%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345644%2Fbest-momo-joints-delhi-recommended-by-foodies-dolma-aunty-majnu-ka-tila-yeti-mood-pema%2F%5C%22%20target